<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 9800 - SPICER 15-1/2 INCH (394 MM) SOLO&#8482; CLUTCH - INSTALL -
        TROUBLESHOOTING
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="troubleshoot" graphiccount="0">
        <title>TROUBLESHOOTING</title>
        <para>The service technician should be able to diagnose a malfunctioning clutch using the following 3-step
            process:
        </para>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Identify the customer's specific "complaint" (condition).</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Investigate the "possible causes" that can be contributing to the customer's complaint.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Perform the appropriate "remedy" to correct the customer's complaint.</para>
        </step1>
        <table id="t1101201">
            <title>Troubleshooting Chart</title>
            <tgroup cols="3">
                <colspec colname="col1" colwidth="1.35in"/>
                <colspec colname="col2" colwidth="1.94in"/>
                <colspec colname="col3" colwidth="3.36in"/>
                <thead>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="col1" align="center">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">Condition</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="col2" align="center">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">Cause</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="col3" align="center">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">Remedy</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                </thead>
                <tbody>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="col1">
                            <para>Clutch Slippage</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="col2">
                            <para>No free pedal.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="col3">
                            <para>Check linkage. Refer to GROUP 11 - LINKAGE in the CTS-5000 Master Service Manual for
                                the model being serviced.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="col1">
                            <para>Clutch Slippage</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="col2">
                            <para>Worn or burned facings.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="col3">
                            <para>Replace driven disc assembly.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="col1">
                            <para>Clutch Slippage</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="col2">
                            <para>Release mechanism binding.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="col3">
                            <para>Free up mechanism and linkage.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="col1">
                            <para>Clutch Slippage</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="col2">
                            <para>Grease or oil on facings.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="col3">
                            <para>Replace driven disc assembly.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="col1">
                            <para>Clutch Slippage</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="col2">
                            <para>Driver riding clutch pedal.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="col3">
                            <para>Refrain from riding clutch pedal.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="col1">
                            <para>Clutch Slippage</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="col2">
                            <para>Overloaded clutch.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="col3">
                            <para>Verify that the proper clutch has been specified for the vehicle's application.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="col1">
                            <para>Poor Release</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="col2">
                            <para>Excessive release bearing travel, causing lever to contact pressure plate (in excess
                                of 5/8 inch).
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="col3">
                            <para>Adjust linkage. Refer to GROUP 11 - LINKAGE in the CTS-5000 Master Service Manual for
                                the model being serviced.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="col1">
                            <para>Poor Release</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="col2">
                            <para>Incorrect pedal height.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="col3">
                            <para>Adjust pedal stop.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="col1">
                            <para>Poor Release</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="col2">
                            <para>No clutch brake squeeze.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="col3">
                            <para>1/2 to 1 inch required.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="col1">
                            <para>Poor Release</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="col2">
                            <para>Damaged bushing in the release bearing sleeve assembly.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="col3">
                            <para>Replace cover.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="col1">
                            <para>Poor Release</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="col2">
                            <para>The intermediate and/or pressure plate is either cracked or broken.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="col3">
                            <para>Replace any damaged parts. This failure is caused by driver abuse or excessive heat as
                                indicated below:
                            </para>
                            <randlist type="bullet">
                                <item>
                                    <para>Holding vehicle on hill with the clutch</para>
                                </item>
                                <item>
                                    <para>Overload</para>
                                </item>
                                <item>
                                    <para>Starting off in wrong gear</para>
                                </item>
                                <item>
                                    <para>Wrong cover assembly installed allowing clutch to slip (misapplication)</para>
                                </item>
                                <item>
                                    <para>Intermediate plate hanging up, allowing clutch to slip.</para>
                                </item>
                            </randlist>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="col1">
                            <para>Poor Release</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="col2">
                            <para>Failure to set the positive separator pins during clutch installation.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="col3">
                            <para>It is important to note that the procedure for setting the positive separator pins can
                                be performed while the transmission is installed. The steps are as follows:
                            </para>
                            <seqlist style="arabic">
                                <item>
                                    <para>Remove the transmission inspection hole cover.</para>
                                </item>
                                <item>
                                    <para>Rotate the clutch cover until one of the holes (for setting the pins) is at
                                        the 6 o'clock position.
                                    </para>
                                </item>
                                <item>
                                    <para>Using the appropriate tool, lightly tap the separator pin to verify that it is
                                        seated against the flywheel.
                                    </para>
                                </item>
                                <item>
                                    <para>Repeat steps 2 and 3 for the remaining three separator pins.</para>
                                </item>
                                <item>
                                    <para>Re-install the transmission inspection hole cover.</para>
                                </item>
                            </seqlist>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="col1">
                            <para>Poor Release</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="col2">
                            <para>The release yoke bridge is contacting the cover assembly at the full release position
                                (clutch pedal to floor).
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="col3">
                            <seqlist style="arabic">
                                <item>
                                    <para>Worn clutch brake.</para>
                                </item>
                                <item>
                                    <para>Broken or missing clutch brake.</para>
                                </item>
                                <item>
                                    <para>Worn or incorrect transmission bearing retaining cap.</para>
                                </item>
                                <item>
                                    <para>Excessive wear on release bearing wear pads and/or the fingers of the yoke.
                                    </para>
                                </item>
                                <item>
                                    <para>Improper set-up of linkage system. Refer to GROUP 11 - LINKAGE in the CTS-5000
                                        Master Service Manual.
                                    </para>
                                </item>
                            </seqlist>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="col1">
                            <para>Poor Release</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="col2">
                            <para>Damaged or non-functioning clutch brake.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="col3">
                            <para>Install new clutch brake when installing a new clutch and/or replace existing brake
                                with 2-piece (Kwik-Konnect type).
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="col1">
                            <para>Poor Release</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="col2">
                            <para>Incorrect use of clutch brake when shifting into 1st gear. Sometimes when applying the
                                clutch brake with the vehicle on a grade, the transmission gears can become locked
                                together due to the applied torque, making it difficult to shift into and out of gear.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="col3">
                            <para>Let up on the clutch pedal a few inches to disengage the clutch brake. Doing so will
                                allow the input shaft to roll over slightly, eliminating the locking condition of the
                                transmission gears and allow for effortless shifting.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="col1">
                            <para>Poor Release</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="col2">
                            <para>Facing of driven disc assemblies are coated with oil or grease.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="col3">
                            <para>Replace the driven disc assemblies. Cleaning of old discs is not recommended.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="col1">
                            <para>Poor Release</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="col2">
                            <para>Rust preventative, i.e., Never Seez, grease, etc. on transmission input drive gear.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="col3">
                            <para>Drive gear should be clean and dry before installing discs.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="col1">
                            <para>Poor Release</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="col2">
                            <para>Release sleeve bushing is contacting the transmission input shaft due to a side
                                loading condition. This condition can be the result of one or more of the following
                                items:
                            </para>
                            <seqlist>
                                <item>
                                    <para>Cross shafts protruding through the release yoke.</para>
                                </item>
                                <item>
                                    <para>Finger(s) of release yoke are bent.</para>
                                </item>
                                <item>
                                    <para>Clutch cover is not mounted concentric.</para>
                                </item>
                                <item>
                                    <para>Misalignment between the transmission bell housing and engine housing.</para>
                                </item>
                                <item>
                                    <para>Loose transmission mounting bolts.</para>
                                </item>
                                <item>
                                    <para>Improper set-up of linkage.</para>
                                </item>
                            </seqlist>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="col3">
                            <seqlist style="alphauc">
                                <item>
                                    <para>Check for protruding cross shafts.</para>
                                </item>
                                <item>
                                    <para>Install a new release yoke.</para>
                                </item>
                                <item>
                                    <para>When mounting clutch cover to the fly wheel, always tighten the mounting bolts
                                        to their proper torque using the crisscross pattern.
                                    </para>
                                </item>
                                <item>
                                    <para>Refer to INSPECTION OF FLYWHEEL AND FLYWHEEL HOUSING for the proper techniques
                                        for checking misalignment.
                                    </para>
                                </item>
                                <item>
                                    <para>Tighten bolts to proper torque.</para>
                                </item>
                                <item>
                                    <para>Thoroughly examine the linkage to determine if it can be contributing to a
                                        side loading condition.
                                    </para>
                                </item>
                            </seqlist>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="col1">
                            <para>Poor Release</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="col2">
                            <para>Driven disc distorted or warped.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="col3">
                            <para>Damage to driven discs can be caused by poor installation methods. Do not force
                                transmission drive gear into disc hubs. This will distort or bend driven disc causing
                                poor release. Also, do not allow transmission to hang unsupported. Replace any distorted
                                or warped discs with new ones.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="col1">
                            <para>Poor Release</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="col2">
                            <para>Disc(s) installed backwards or front and rear discs were switched with each other.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="col3">
                            <para>Install new discs. Also, investigate the clutch cover for any damage. Replace if
                                damaged.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="col1">
                            <para>Poor Release</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="col2">
                            <para>Spline worn on main drive gear of transmission.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="col3">
                            <para>Replace drive gear and check driven disc hubs for excessive wear. If worn, replace
                                disc. Check flywheel housing alignment of engine and transmission. Make sure driven
                                discs slide freely on drive gear splines.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="col1">
                            <para>Poor Release</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="col2">
                            <para>Flywheel pilot bearing fits either too tight or too loose in the flywheel and/or end
                                of input shaft.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="col3">
                            <para>Check pilot bearing for proper fit.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="col1">
                            <para>Poor Release</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="col2">
                            <para>Damaged or dry (rough) pilot bearing.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="col3">
                            <para>Replace with new bearing.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="col1">
                            <para>Poor Release</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="col2">
                            <para>Foreign material on the internal workings of the clutch cover.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="col3">
                            <para>Remove foreign material. Ensure that the transmission inspection hole cover is
                                re-installed to minimize future problems.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="col1">
                            <para>Poor Release</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="col2">
                            <para>Excessive flywheel runout.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="col3">
                            <para>Reface or replace flywheel.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="col1">
                            <para>Poor Release</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="col2">
                            <para>Corrosion of disc hubs to transmission input shaft.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="col3">
                            <para>Clean the mating parts to ensure that the discs slide freely over input shaft.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="col1">
                            <para>Poor Release</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="col2">
                            <para>Engine idling too fast.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="col3">
                            <para>Re-adjust engine to proper idling speed.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="col1">
                            <para>Noisy/ rattling</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="col2">
                            <para>Clutch release bearing is dry or damaged.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="col3">
                            <para>Lubricate the bearing. If the noise persists, install a new clutch cover (the release
                                bearing will be included with the cover).
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="col1">
                            <para>Noisy/ rattling</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="col2">
                            <para>Flywheel pilot bearing is dry or damaged.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="col3">
                            <para>Replace.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="col1">
                            <para>Noisy/ rattling</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="col2">
                            <para>Failure to use the transmission inspection hole cover.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="col3">
                            <para>Re-install the cover.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="col1">
                            <para>Noisy/ rattling</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="col2">
                            <para>Worn sleeve bushing.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="col3">
                            <para>Investigate for any side loading conditions on the release bearing housing. Determine
                                the cause, being sure to correct before installing the new clutch.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="col1">
                            <para>Noisy/ rattling</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="col2">
                            <para>The linkage system is frozen, improperly lubricated, worn excessively, has missing
                                parts (washers, etc.) or the linkage itself is rattling excessively.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="col3">
                            <para>Clean, lubricate and reassemble or replace missing/worn parts.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="col1">
                            <para>Vibrating clutch</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="col2">
                            <para>Loose flywheel.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="col3">
                            <para>Retighten flywheel mounting bolts to the proper specifications.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="col1">
                            <para>Vibrating clutch</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="col2">
                            <para>Worn universal joints.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="col3">
                            <para>Replace worn parts.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="col1">
                            <para>Vibrating clutch</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="col2">
                            <para>Improper phasing of driveshaft.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="col3">
                            <para>Investigate for correct yoke phasing.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="col1">
                            <para>Vibrating clutch</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="col2">
                            <para>Driveshaft is not balanced.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="col3">
                            <para>Balance and straighten driveshaft. Also, ensure that no balance weights have come off
                                the driveshaft.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="col1">
                            <para>Vibrating clutch</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="col2">
                            <para>Incorrect driveline angles.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="col3">
                            <para>Shim drivetrain components to equalize U-joint angles.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="col1">
                            <para>Vibrating clutch</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="col2">
                            <para>Flywheel is not balanced.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="col3">
                            <para>Balance the flywheel.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="col1">
                            <para>Vibrating clutch</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="col2">
                            <para>Damaged, loose or worn out engine mounts.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="col3">
                            <para>Replace any damaged/worn parts. Retighten all loose bolts to proper specifications.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="col1">
                            <para>Vibrating clutch</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="col2">
                            <para>Excessive flywheel run-out.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="col3">
                            <para>Reface or replace flywheel.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="col1">
                            <para>Premature Wear</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="col2">
                            <para>Riding of clutch pedal, causing premature wear.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="col3">
                            <para>Replace clutch and instruct driver on correct operation.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="col1">
                            <para>Premature Wear</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="col2">
                            <para>Holding the vehicle on an incline by using the slipping clutch as a brake. Doing this
                                can cause premature wear.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="col3">
                            <para>Replace clutch and instruct driver on correct operation.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="col1">
                            <para>Chattering/</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="col2">
                            <para>Input shaft spline wear.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="col3">
                            <para>Replace input shaft.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="col1">
                            <para>Erratic Engagement/ Clutch Grabs</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="col2">
                            <para>Clutch is worn out: the driven disc assembly(s) have worn down to the facing rivets.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="col3">
                            <para>Replace all worn components.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="col1">
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="col2">
                            <para>The linkage system is not operating freely; it is binding and/or worn excessively.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="col3">
                            <para>Replace all worn parts, being sure to lubricate.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="col1">
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="col2">
                            <para>Grease/oil on the disc(s) facing material.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="col3">
                            <para>Replace disc(s).</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="col1">
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="col2">
                            <para>Loose engine mounts.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="col3">
                            <para>Refer to GROUP 12 - ENGINE in the CTS-5000 Master Service Manual for the engine mount
                                torque specifications for the vehicle being serviced.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="col1">
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="col2">
                            <para>The fingers of the release yoke and/or the wear pads on the release bearing are worn
                                excessively.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="col3">
                            <para>Replace all worn parts.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="col1">
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="col2">
                            <para>Starting in incorrect gear.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="col3">
                            <para>Use 1st gear. Engine idle is not correct.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="col1">
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="col2">
                            <para>Insufficient startability for load or terrain.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="col3">
                            <para>Contact OEM.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                </tbody>
            </tgroup>
        </table>
